    <div class="rem-def" style="text-align: center; font-size:20px;">
        <p style="text-align: left;">Hyperacidity, also known as acid dyspepsia, is a common issue bothering most of the people. It is a medical disorder where the stomach produces an excess of acids, mainly hydrochloric by the gastric glands.<br><br>Hyperacidity is the result of an imbalance between the acid-secreting mechanism of the stomach and intestine and the shielding mechanism that provides safety. Generally, the stomach secretes hydrochloric acid which aids in the breaking down of food into smaller substances, thereby promoting the digestion process. However, when there is an excess build-up of hydrochloric acid in the stomach it leads to hyperactivity.</p>
    </div>

